# InceptBench

Educational content evaluation tool with comprehensive AI-powered assessment. Automatically selects and runs appropriate evaluation methods based on your content characteristics.

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/inceptbench.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/inceptbench)
[![Python Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/inceptbench.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/inceptbench/)
[![License: Proprietary](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Proprietary-red.svg)](LICENSE)

**Repository**: [https://github.com/trilogy-group/inceptbench](https://github.com/trilogy-group/inceptbench)

## Features

ğŸ¯ **Unified Evaluation Interface**
- Single evaluator that automatically routes to appropriate assessment methods
- Intelligent evaluation selection based on subject, grade, and content type
- Comprehensive quality scoring across multiple dimensions
- Support for both questions and text content

ğŸ“Š **Flexible Output**
- Simplified mode (default) for quick score viewing - ~95% smaller output
- Full mode (`--full`) with all detailed metrics, issues, strengths, and reasoning
- Append mode (`-a`) for collecting multiple evaluations
- JSON output for easy integration

ğŸš€ **Easy to Use**
- Simple CLI interface with optional routing parameters
- Runs locally with OpenAI and Anthropic API integrations
- Batch processing support
- High-throughput benchmark mode for parallel evaluation
- Automatic evaluation method selection

## Installation

```bash
pip install inceptbench

# Or upgrade to latest version
pip install inceptbench --upgrade --no-cache-dir
```

## Quick Start

### 1. Set up API Keys

Create a `.env` file in your working directory:

```bash
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_key
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_key
HUGGINGFACE_TOKEN=your_hf_token  # Optional for EduBench tasks
```

### 2. Generate Sample File

```bash
inceptbench example
```

This creates `qs.json` with a complete example question.

### 3. Evaluate

```bash
# Simplified output (default) - evaluator auto-selects methods
inceptbench evaluate qs.json

# Specify subject and grade for better routing
inceptbench evaluate qs.json --subject math --grade "6-8"

# With progress messages
inceptbench evaluate qs.json --verbose

# Full detailed output
inceptbench evaluate qs.json --full --verbose
```

## Usage

### Commands

#### `evaluate` - Evaluate educational content

```bash
# Basic evaluation (evaluator auto-selects methods)
inceptbench evaluate questions.json

# Specify subject for specialized evaluation
inceptbench evaluate questions.json --subject math

# With grade level for better routing
inceptbench evaluate questions.json --subject ela --grade "6-8"

# Specify content type
inceptbench evaluate questions.json --type mcq

# Full detailed evaluation results
inceptbench evaluate questions.json --full

# Save results to file (overwrite)
inceptbench evaluate questions.json -o results.json

# Append results to file (creates if not exists)
inceptbench evaluate questions.json -a all_evaluations.json --verbose

# Complete example with all parameters
inceptbench evaluate questions.json --subject math --grade "6" --full --verbose
```

**Optional Parameters:**
- `--subject, -s`: Subject area (`math`, `ela`, `science`, `social-studies`, `general`)
- `--grade, -g`: Grade level (e.g., `"K"`, `"3"`, `"6-8"`, `"9-12"`)
- `--type`: Content type (`mcq`, `fill-in`, `short-answer`, `essay`, `text-content`, `passage`)
- `--full, -f`: Return full detailed evaluation (default: simplified scores only)
- `--verbose, -v`: Show progress messages

#### `example` - Generate sample input file

```bash
# Generate qs.json (default)
inceptbench example

# Save to custom filename
inceptbench example -o sample.json
```

#### `benchmark` - High-throughput parallel evaluation

Process many questions in parallel for maximum throughput. Perfect for evaluating large datasets.

```bash
# Basic benchmark (100 parallel workers by default)
inceptbench benchmark questions.json

# With subject and grade parameters
inceptbench benchmark questions.json --subject math --grade "6-8"

# Custom worker count
inceptbench benchmark questions.json --workers 50

# Save results with verbose output
inceptbench benchmark questions.json -o results.json --verbose

# Complete example
inceptbench benchmark questions.json --subject ela --workers 200 -o results.json --verbose
```

**Benchmark Output:**
```json
{
  "request_id": "uuid",
  "total_questions": 100,
  "successful": 98,
  "failed": 2,
  "scores": [
    {
      "id": "q1",
      "score": 0.91,
      "scores": {
        "ti_question_qa": {"overall": 0.93},
        "answer_verification": {"is_correct": true},
        "reading_question_qc": {"overall_score": 0.8}
      }
    }
  ],
  "failed_ids": ["q42", "q87"],
  "evaluation_time_seconds": 45.3,
  "avg_score": 0.89
}
```

#### `help` - Show detailed help

```bash
inceptbench help
```

## Input Format

The input JSON file should contain your educational content. The evaluator automatically selects appropriate evaluation methods based on your content and optional parameters.

**Required Fields:**
- `generated_questions`: Array of questions to evaluate, OR
- `generated_content`: Array of text content to evaluate

**Optional Routing Parameters:**
- `subject`: Subject area (`"math"`, `"ela"`, `"science"`, `"social-studies"`, `"general"`)
- `grade`: Grade level (e.g., `"K"`, `"3"`, `"6-8"`, `"9-12"`)
- `type`: Content type (`"mcq"`, `"fill-in"`, `"short-answer"`, `"essay"`, `"text-content"`, `"passage"`)

**Example:**

```json
{
  "subject": "math",
  "grade": "6",
  "generated_questions": [
